Descripción
MISSION

The Editor in Chief is responsible for the strategy, management, and development of data driven digital articles, press releases, whitepapers, and all other content on a blog. The Editor in Chief is also a public-facing role and a brand representative at selected events.

The Editor in Chief is expected to ensure that web and social media-based content is fresh and relevant. Among other things, this will include creating an editorial calendar that highlights the major events and themes for coverage, under the guidance of the senior management team, and guiding a team of creative designers, data analysts and other data science professionals to produce and post content.

The right candidate is strategic, organized, tenacious, calm under pressure, and able to juggle numerous tasks, as you will be involved in all areas of editorial operation. The ability to effectively plan and execute a detailed editorial approach is critical.

Build and maintain a positive public image for the company, though representing (and building relationships) it as the main contact for the media. Handle all dealings with digital and social media as well as track media coverage related to the company. Create international awareness of the brand through PR activities, trying to capture the interest of journalists, agencies and newswires on our company’s activities and campaigns. Shape public opinion on the company in alignment with our corporate goals.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Working under the senior management team to guide and fulfill the editorial vision for the company across digital and social media channels (website, blog, Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, etc.)
Writing stories and producing multimedia content across platforms at the appropriate volumes required.
Guiding a multidisciplinary team of analysts, writers, visual artists and contributors from operational teams for content development and publishing across channels
Collaborating with the rest of the quality control team to maximize and optimize content output
Collaborating with the commercial team on branded content projects
Representing the company at industry and brand events

CANDIDATE PROFILE

Education
Bachelor or Masters degree in Journalism, PR, marketing, or a related field;
Preferably with a degree (or at least some semesters) of education abroad (USA, Europe, Australia)

Experience Requirements
Superb writing and oral english skills
5+ years of experience working in an editorial / mass communication organization
Experience handling a press conference and other PR related activities
Experience working with media agencies, massive communication, or newswires
Experience pitching to media representatives
At least five years of experience in a premium editorial environment and multiple years of editorial leadership experience
Experience working on mass communication publication, ideally in both print and digital editorial teams.
Curiosity and passion towards learning about technology driven marketing, big data and consumer / market insights.
Strong understanding of online publishing and digital platforms
Results-oriented personality and demonstrated track record
Strong relationship-building skills
Excellent oral and written communication skills
High energy and passion

SKILLS

Fluently bilingual (written, spoken, listen);
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Ability to write articles related to mass audiences (entertainment, informative journalism, sports, politics, etc.). Writing samples will be requested.
Ability to think both creatively and strategically;
Enthusiastic learning;
Ability to run PR campaigns that deliver measurable results and meet objectives;
Project and budget management skills;
Social Media understanding;
Open to team working and collaboration;
Open to multi-tasking and changes;
Problem solving mindset;
Proactive;
Leadership abilities;
Highly organized;
Research oriented;
